Assumes gaussian width of 3, uses Brocher '05 for crust density & vp but mantle parameters (see Shen et al) for mantle Vp and rho
Also, enforces positive jump into Moho and upper mantle must be increasing


do_MC_Para.C:

Read in FILE: F.CONTROL
Out put FILE: BIN.XX, BIN.XX.1, MC.XX.out, MC.XX.mod

do_MC_Para_Post_process_v1.C:
Read in FILE: F.CONTROL
Out put FILE: MC.XXX.acc.average.?, MC.XXX.minmisfit.? ...


INPUT FILE:

in.model

0 4 1 2 1. 2.5 1 2 2.0
1 2 54 4 3.2 3.3 3.6 3.7 1 3 1.75
2 2 145 5 4.3 4.2 4.2 4.4 4.5 2 0 1.75

Column 1: ids of the layer (0,1,2)
COlumn 2: parameterization type flag: (4: linear; 2: cubic B-splines; 1: Layerized)
Column 3: thickness of each layer
Column 4: number of values that describe the layer (2 for linear, N for B-spline, N for layerized)
Column 5-5+N(2): values that describe the layer
Column -3: Rflag, 1(Brocher's 2005 paper); 2(Perturbation relative to reference velocity) 3(1.05, for water)
Column -2: Qflag, 0(input), 1(water: 0/57882); 2(sediment,160/80); 3(crust,600/1368), 4(mantle,417/1008)
Column -1: Vp/Vs ratio for the layer


in.para
0 1 1. 0.04 0 0 
0 1 1. 0.04 0 1
0 -1 20 0.04 1 0
0 -1 20 0.04 1 1
0 -1 20 0.04 1 2
0 -1 20 0.04 1 3
0 -1 15 0.04 2 0
0 -1 15 0.04 2 1
0 -1 15 0.04 2 2
0 -1 15 0.04 2 3
0 -1 15 0.04 2 4
1 -1 100 0.05 0
1 1 15 0.5 1

Column 1: id_flag: 0(values to be perturbed), 1(thickness to be perturbed)
Column 2: pertur_flag 1(absolute perturbation), -1(relative perturbation in percentage)
Column 3: perturbation range
Column 4: gaussian step width
Column 5: layer id
Column 6: value id
